# Decision log

Time-ordered log of decisions per Purpose / cycle. Used to trace why a hypothesis was
dropped, why a Purpose was opened or split off, or why a particular method was chosen,
after the fact.

A "cycle" here is one notebook (= one Purpose). A Purpose with multiple H's
yields a single cycle entry with H sub-bullets, not one entry per H.

The Purpose entry also carries the research-goal layer's bookkeeping: the
**design hypothesis** at open and at close (the prediction "this Purpose
closes such-and-such sub-claims"), and the **sub-claim progress update**
applied to the project README's sub-claim list. See
`references/research_goal_layer.md`.

## Format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD cycle <N> (exp_<NNN>_<purpose-slug>) — Purpose: <one-line>

- **Design hypothesis at open**: [the prediction made BEFORE the cycle ran —
  which research-goal sub-claim(s) this Purpose is expected to advance, and
  in what direction. Example: "Opening this Purpose will close G1.1 (quality
  factor yields net edge in TOPIX500) to either confirmed or falsified
  regardless of per-H verdict pattern. It does NOT touch G1.2 or G1.3
  directly."]

- **Tested H<id>**: [one-line restatement, with target_sub_claim_id]
  - Observation: [observed values, anomalies]
  - Verdict: [supported / rejected / partial / parked]
  - Robustness battery (this H): [pass / fail per item in robustness_battery.md]
- **Tested H<id+1> (derived from H<id>, same Purpose)**: [one-line restatement,
  with target_sub_claim_id; if it differs from parent's, give the override
  reason]
  - Observation: ...
  - Verdict: ...
  - Robustness battery (this H): ...
- **Tested H<id+2>** (...): ...

- **Purpose-level synthesis**: [one or two sentences across all H's tested.
  Pattern (A-E) match per `cross_h_synthesis.md`, primary closure form
  (Primary YES / Fallback NO with binding axis / KICK-UP).]

- **Research-goal sub-claim progress update**: [for each sub-claim this
  Purpose touched, state the transition.
  - G1.1: in progress → confirmed (H2 met YES branch with WF mean = 0.41)
  - G1.2: not started → not started (no Purpose has attacked this yet)
  - G1.3: not started → not started
  Sub-claims that were not touched are still listed (= still `not started`)
  so the project's running state is fully visible at every cycle.]

- **Design hypothesis at close**: [verification of the at-open prediction.
  CONFIRMED / FALSIFIED / PARTIAL, with one-phrase reason. The next Purpose's
  selection is justified from this line, not from the per-H numeric
  observations alone. Example: "CONFIRMED — G1.1 advanced to confirmed as
  predicted; G1.2 and G1.3 are unchanged, as predicted."]

- **Derived Purposes** (= candidates for new notebooks):
  - P<new> (target_sub_claim_id = G1.<X>): [brief, with which sub-claim it
    will attack and why]
  - P<new> (target_sub_claim_id = G1.<Y>): ...

- **Direction rejected**: [what was tried inside this Purpose and did not work,
  with reason]
```

Note: classification of derived H's (run-now / next-session / drop) is **not**
written here. That belongs in `hypotheses.md`'s `Status` column
(`planned-runnow` / `planned-nextsession` / `planned-drop`) — single source
of truth for H-level planning state. The `Derived Purposes` section above
is for Purpose-level (= new-notebook) candidates only.

## Example

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD cycle 5 (pur_005_mean_reversion_eurusd_intraday) — Purpose: Mean-reversion at H1 frequency on EUR/USD generates risk-adjusted edge net of cost

- **Design hypothesis at open**: opening this Purpose will close G1.1 (mean-reversion
  exists on EUR/USD intraday at signal-strength sufficient to produce a verdict)
  to either confirmed or falsified. It does NOT touch G1.2 (turnover / live-tradeability)
  or G1.3 (cross-asset generalization) directly.

- **Tested H3**: entry filter × signal-flip exit beats fee 0.5 bp/side (target_sub_claim_id = G1.1)
  - Observation:
    - val Sharpe +0.52 (fee 1 bp), +1.45 (fee 0)
    - win 62.4 % (val) / 62.3 % (test) — preserved across the split
    - Walk-forward mean Sharpe -0.10, pct_positive 47.4 % (unstable)
    - Bootstrap 95 % CI = [0.009, 0.202], p = 0.014 — significant but small effect size
  - Verdict: partial (negative at fee 1 bp, borderline at 0.5 bp, walk-forward unstable)
  - Robustness battery (H3): 4 of 7 passed (threshold ✓ / fee ✓ / bootstrap CI border /
    walk-forward ✗ / DSR not computed / realistic cost not run / regime not run)

- **Tested H10 (derived from H3, same Purpose)**: vol-targeted size to stabilize walk-forward
  (target_sub_claim_id = G1.1, inherited from H3)
  - Observation: walk-forward pct_positive 0.474 → 0.71, val Sharpe slightly down (1.45 → 1.18)
    at fee 0; test Sharpe 0.62 → 0.55
  - Verdict: supported (walk-forward stability gate met; test Sharpe acceptable)
  - Robustness battery (H10): 6 of 7 passed (regime not run)

- **Purpose-level synthesis**: mean-reversion works on EUR/USD intraday only with
  vol-targeted sizing (H10); fixed sizing (H3) is fragile across walk-forward windows.
  Pattern D (monotonic improvement, latest H supported); closure = Primary YES.

- **Research-goal sub-claim progress update**:
  - G1.1: in progress → confirmed (H10 met YES branch under vol-targeted sizing)
  - G1.2: not started → not started (turnover / capacity not tested in this Purpose)
  - G1.3: not started → not started (single-asset only)

- **Design hypothesis at close**: CONFIRMED — G1.1 advanced to confirmed as predicted.
  Note: the H3 → H10 transition (need for vol-targeted sizing) was a refinement
  *inside* G1.1, not a shift to G1.2; the at-open prediction held.

- **Derived Purposes**:
  - P_momentum_eurusd_intraday (target_sub_claim_id = none — different research goal,
    flag as candidate for project-level scope expansion): is the inverse phenomenon
    (continuation) profitable on the same universe?
  - P_meanrev_jpypairs (target_sub_claim_id = G1.3): test G1.3 on JPY-cross intraday;
    different cross-section ⇒ new notebook.
  - P_meanrev_eurusd_capacity (target_sub_claim_id = G1.2): take the H10 strategy and
    test live-tradeability constraints; this is the next sub-claim to attack.

- **Direction rejected**: time-stop alone as exit (effect size < fee). Reason: signal
  horizon and exit horizon do not coincide.
```

## Notes

- Do not delete. Negative results stay.
- Use specific numbers ("Sharpe -1.74" rather than "Sharpe was low")
- The "Research-goal sub-claim progress update" section is mandatory at every
  Purpose closure, even when no sub-claim status changed (still listing them
  as unchanged is what makes the project's running state visible)
- The "Design hypothesis at close" line marks the at-open prediction as
  CONFIRMED / FALSIFIED / PARTIAL — falsified is a legitimate research
  output, not a process failure
- Per-H planning state (run-now / next-session / drop) lives in
  `hypotheses.md`'s `Status` column, not here
- Per-Purpose entries replace the older per-H entries; multiple H's belong as
  sub-bullets under one Purpose entry
